# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Protoype chain, just use this chain.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The checkIfInstanceOf function determines if an object (`obj`) is an instance of a specific class or a class that inherits from it (`classFunction`).

To achieve this, the function iterates through the prototype chain of the object (`obj`) using a while loop.

Just before the loop we create varibale `p` and store in initial `__proto__` of the `obj` there.

At each iteration, it compares the current (`p`) to the prototype of the class (`classFunction.prototype`).

If a match is found, we return true. Otherwise, we set `p.__proto__` to the itself and keep the loop until finding a match.

Wnen the last `__proto__` is null thne loop is being stopped and then we return false;

# Complexity
- Time complexity: n/a
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: n/a
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
/**
 * @param {any} obj
 * @param {any} classFunction
 * @return {boolean}
 */
var checkIfInstanceOf = function(obj, classFunction) {
  let p = obj?.__proto__;
  while (p) {
    if (p === classFunction?.prototype) {
      return true;
    }
    p = p?.__proto__;
  }
  return false;
};

/**
 * checkIfInstanceOf(new Date(), Date); // true
 */
```

