# Approach
JavaScript is `Prototybe Based` Language which means it handles inheritence with Prototype Chain.
So we will start to ask if `Obj` & `classFunction` are the same constructor ?. if yes then `true` else we will make `obj` points to the value of it's parent prototybe or in another word.
If the obj isn't the same as `classFunction` we will check if his father is.

And so on till we either find that they are the same or break the loop when we reached the end.

